This paper is about modeling plasticity in artificial neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of neural networks and learning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of reinforcement signals and genetic algorithms, which are common in the fields of machine learning and artificial intelligence, respectively. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with the problem of delayed reinforcement signals, which is relevant to the field of control systems and robotics, hence cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach to synaptic plasticity, which could be of interest to researchers in the field of robotics, hence cs.RO (Robotics) is a possible sub-category.
